Packages with Storybook for Flutter\nDate: 2024-03-02\nURL: https://zenn.dev/ima
joriri/articles/6b10a2351fe887?locale=en\nSummary:  Introduction\n\n GitHub Page
s\n\nSince Flutter Web is a web technology, GitHub Pages can be used. However, I
decided against it because managing viewing permissions on GitHub seemed like it
would be a hassle.\n\nIt seems to be a good fit for public personal development 
repositories.\n\nI actually set up a GitHub Action to deploy to GitHub Pages for
this project.\n\n AWS S3 — We Chose This\n\nAnother possibility is an external h
osting environment like S3, and fortunately, we already had an S3 environment av
ailable for anyone within the company to use.\n\nRegarding accessibility, it is 
an environment that anyone can view as long as they are connected to the VPN.\n\
nTherefore, we decided to use S3 this time.\n\nS3 can also be deployed via GitHu
b Actions, and we have set up an Action like the one below.\n\nThe trigger is se
t to when a merge occurs in the `develop` branch, and it only runs when there ar
e changes in\n\n## Introduction\n\n### GitHub Pages\n\nSince Flutter Web is a we
b technology, GitHub Pages can be used. However, I decided against it because ma
naging viewing permissions on GitHub seemed like it would be a hassle.\n\nIt see
ms to be a good fit for public personal development repositories.\n\nI actually 
